==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Kinematics
<hw>Kin`e*mat"ics</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. (<?/),(<?/)
motion, fr. <grk>kinei^n</grk> to move.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld>
<def>The science which treats of motions considered in themselves, or
apart from their causes; the comparison and relation of
motions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Kinematics forms properly an introduction to mechanics,
as involving the mathematical principles which are to be applied to its
data of forces.</note> <rj><au>Nichol.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kinepox</ent>⟦br⟧
